&lt;?php mysql_connect(&quot;db_host&quot;,&quot;db_user&quot;,&quot;db_pass&quot;); mysql_select_db(&quot;db_name&quot;); ?&gt;  Where db_host, db_user, db_pass and db_name is the host, username, password and name for your database respectively.
General practice is to save the code in a separate file in the &lsquo;includes&rsquo; folder and including it on the page where you need it.
&lt;?php include(&quot;database.php&quot;) ?&gt;
